<HEAD>Bus Crash Kills 18 In Peru</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus plunged off a mountain highway and
tumbled 140 feet down a river embankment, killing 18 people and
injuring 34, police said.
   The private bus crashed Tuesday near Pucara, 510 miles north of
Lima, police said Wednesday.
   Police said many of the passengers were tossed from the rolling
vehicle before it halted on the banks of the Huancabamba river.
   The bus was en route from the jungle city of Jaen to Chiclayo, a
coastal capital located 110 miles to the southwest, police said.
</TEXT>
