<HEAD>Archbishop Says He Was Stopped From Leaving Liberia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONROVIA, Liberia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Episcopalian archbishop of Liberia,
the Most Rev. George Browne, said authorities prevented him from
leaving the country.
   Browne, an outspoken critic of the government of President
Samuel Doe, said Wednesday that he was stopped at the country's
international airport on Saturday by officials who prevented him
from boarding his plane.
   He said he wrote to Justice Minister Jenkins Scott for an
explanation but had yet to receive a reply. Browne said he was
going to neighboring Guinea to ordain some priests when he was
stopped.
   Doe, a former master sergeant, took power in a military coup in
1980.
