<HEAD>Teacher Stabs Four Colleagues After Denied Promotion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teacher who was denied promotion
stabbed and wounded four colleagues, police said.
   Hwang In-su, 46, an English teacher at a high school near the
southern city of Chonju, on Tuesday pulled a knife and attempted to
attack the principal after Hwang was passed over for promotion,
police said Wednesday.
   The principal escaped, but four teachers in the office were
stabbed, police said. The four were reported in fair condition.
   Police said Hwang had been charged with attempted murder.
