<2ND_LINE>PM-Grammys-Diana Ross,0217</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Diana Ross Says She and Mary Wilson Still Aren't Friends</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Grammys, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Diana Ross says she still isn't talking with
Mary Wilson, her former partner in the Supremes.
   Talking with reporters at the 30th Annual Grammy Awards on
Wednesday, Miss Ross also said she wished she could have been at
the recent Rock 'n' Roll Hall of Fame banquet for the induction of
the Supremes.
   ``I wasn't able to get there. The baby, the whole thing, I
really couldn't get there,'' she said.
   Miss Wilson and a daughter of the third original Supreme, the
late Florence Ballard, attended the induction.
   Asked whether she and Miss Wilson are talking, Miss Ross said,
``No.''
   ``I'm really a good person,'' she added. ``I could be real good.
Somebody slaps you and slaps you and you'll still be good?''
   Told that Miss Wilson had said in Los Angeles that she's like to
renew the friendship, Miss Ross said, ``Of course she would feel
that way.''
   She said she hadn't read Miss Wilson's autobiography, ``but I
think she said kind of not really nice things. Insinuations in the
book were not nice to me. And I was really hurt by it.''
</TEXT>
