<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Thursday by
participants in the two-day NATO summit.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>PRESIDENT REAGAN:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   ``All of us understand the absolute necessity of maintaining the
credibility of our deterrent. We will never trade that credibility
away at the negotiating table and we won't give it away through
neglect.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>FRANCOIS MITTERAND, France:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   ``We must not be naive, but we must show flexibility, which will
enable dialogue, which will have an effect on (Soviet leader
Mikhail S.) Gorbachev's actions,'' Mitterand was quoted as telling
his fellow summiteers.
   
   MARGARET THATCHER, Britain, on modernizing NATO's nuclear
arsenal:
   ``Everyone in that room recognized that you don't deter with
obsolete or obsolescent weapons ... It is ridiculous to say that
you do.''
   
