   He said this was ``absolutely not the time to talk about
modernization. It will not be necessary to do it before'' the early
1990s.
   
   PRIME MINISTER RUDD LUBBERS, Netherlands:
   ``(The communique) gives the flexibility to choose the moment
and where and how to modernize.''
   
   FOREIGN MINISTER GIOVANNI ANDREOTTI, Italy, on the NATO
communique:
   ``The basis for the statement is political cohesion coupled with
military readiness.''
