<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--BiscuitMurder     03-03 0122</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Biscuit Murder,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Argument Over Biscuits Prompts Shooting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOBILE, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A drunken argument between two men over the
edibility of the food they were eating ended with one man shot
dead, and his nephew has been charged with murder, authorities said.
   Robert E. New Jr., 19, was being held in the Mobile County Jail
today on a murder charge in the Wednesday slaying of his uncle,
James Gilbert New, 59, a jailer said.
   ``It appears the men were drinking all day and they began to
argue over the quality of the biscuits they were eating,'' said
Sheriff Tom Purvis. ``Sometimes it doesn't take a lot to set some
people off.''
   Purvis said the shooting occurred at the uncle's home.
</TEXT>
