<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Obit-Alston     03-03 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Alston,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Carter Confidant Dies At 76</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Philip Henry Alston Jr., a confidant of former
President Jimmy Carter and former ambassador to Australia, has
died. He was 76.
   Alston died Wednesday after a short illness.
   An influential Atlanta lawyer, Alston raised millions of dollars
for the University of Georgia and began supporting Carter
politically after meeting him in 1966.
   Carter lost the governor's race that year to Lester Maddox, but
Alston was chairman of Carter's successful gubernatorial bid in
1970. He was chairman of the Committee for Jimmy Carter when Carter
was elected president in 1976.
   As president, Carter appointed Alston ambassador to Australia.
   Survivors include his wife, a son, a daughter and five
grandchildren.
</TEXT>
