<HEAD>9-Year-Old Dies in Dryer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANKAKEE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The body of a 9-year-old boy, handcuffed
and naked, was found inside the family's clothes dryer, authorities
said Thursday.
   The death of the boy, James L. Keller, appears to have been
accidental but the investigation was incomplete, said Deputy Police
Chief Robert Pepin.
   He said police were called to the home Wednesday night and
officers found the parents trying to revive the boy.
   ``As near as we can tell,'' said Pepin, ``he had been playing
with a couple of siblings and somehow or other ended up in the
dryer.''
   Kankakee County Coroner James Orrison said there were some burns
on the body, indicating the dryer had been turned on, but that he
had not determined the cause of death.
   Police do not know why the boy was naked and his hands cuffed.
Pepin said the accident happened in the basement while the father
was sleeping and the mother was out of the house.
   Earlier this week, the body of a 12-year-old Humboldt, Wis., boy
was found nude in a portable dishwasher that had been turned on.
Police said the death was apparently accidental but they were
continuing to investigate.
