<HEAD>Brigitte Nielsen Says Business is Better After Marriage to
Stallone</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Brigitte Nielsen says she has no regrets
about marrying Sylvester Stallone _ it was good for business.
   ``I have more success than I've ever had,'' Nielsen, who has
since split from the ``Rocky'' star, says in the March 21 issue of
Us magazine. ``So whatever I have done, I must have done something
right because I'm doing good, and more important, I feel good.''
   She adds that ``my business was terrific whether I was married
or not'' but ``it might have taken longer'' to make it if she had
not married the actor.
   ``To stay on top, you have got to have personality and talent,''
she says. ``Then it doesn't matter who you were married to.''
   Adding that she wants to be taken seriously, Nielsen says it is
``frustrating to be seen as a bimbo.''
   Nielsen is engaged to Jets defensive lineman Mark Gastineau.
