<HEAD>Town Gives Tongue-In-Cheek Invite To Swaggart, Tammy Bakker and
Robertson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WENATCHEE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fallen TV evangelists Jimmy Swaggart and
Tammy Bakker have been invited to be hosts of the annual Loyal
Order of Hibernians parade, but organizers say they won't be
surprised if the answer is no.
   Last year organizers invited Lt. Col. Oliver North to be grand
marshal of the half-block long St. Patrick's Day parade. The year
before it was deposed Philippine President Ferdinand Marcos.
Neither accepted.
   This year they want Swaggart, who stepped down from his pulpit
after tearfully admitting that he had sinned, to be grand marshal,
said Mayor Jim Lynch.
   They want Mrs. Bakker, wife of former PTL evangelist Jim Bakker,
to be parade queen. Bakker stepped down last year after revelations
of sex and hush money.
   ``We had a little dissension on that, but one of the guys said
if she wore green eye shade it would be OK,'' Lynch said.
   They also want Republican presidental candidate Pat Robertson, a
former TV minister, in charge of publicity.
   ``He has a good Irish bent for saying the first thing that comes
to his mind,'' Lynch said. ``We like him because he's not too
bothered with facts.''
