<HEAD>Reagan's Comment on Contra Vote</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The text of a written statement by President
Reagan commenting on the House's defeat of a Democratic plan for
``humanitarian'' aid for the Contras and for young victims of the
Nicaragua war:
   The House has once again failed to approve an aid package for
the Nicaraguan Democratic Resistance. I call on the House and
Senate to act urgently to develop an aid package which is
effectively deliverable and of sufficient quantity to sustain the
Nicaraguan freedom fighters. If not, the prospects for peace and
democracy inside Nicaragua will diminish quickly.
