<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Senegal-Elections     03-03 0127</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Senegal-Elections,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Diouf's Election Confirmed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAKAR, Senegal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Supreme Court on Thursday confirmed
President Abdou Diouf's re-election to a second, five-year term
with 73 percent of the vote.
   Diouf won Sunday's elections with 828,301 of the 1,135,501 votes
cast. His nearest opponent, Abdoulaye Wade of the Senegalese
Democratic Party, polled 291,869 votes or 26 percent, said a
communique.
   Two other candidates split the remaining votes.
   Results for the 120-seat National Assembly were to be announced
later. Diouf's party had a lopsided majority in the old assembly.
   Opposition leaders, including Wade, claimed the voting was
rigged. They have been detained since violent clashes between
stone-throwing youths and riot police broke out Monday and Tuesday.
The violence followed a preliminary government announcement that
Diouf was re-elected.
</TEXT>
