<HEAD>Rebels Burn Down Police Detachment, Kidnap Policeman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 200 leftist rebels raided a
northern mountain village, set fire to a police detachment and
kidnapped a policeman, the military said Friday.
   A report at the Philippine Constabulary headquarters in the
capital said the attack by the communist New People's Army rebels
occurred Thursday in Sadanga, about 180 miles north of Manila.
   It said police manning the outpost put up a brief fight but
surrendered after two defenders were wounded. The report said the
rebels confiscated police firearms, burned down the outpost and
took a patrolman, Helbert Pacho, as a hostage before fleeing to the
forest.
   A separate group of rebels ambushed reinforcements from a nearby
police station, but the report did not say whether casualties
resulted.
   The communists have been fighting to overthrow the government
for 19 years.
