<TEXT>
   Irish rockers U2 led the new wave with two
awards at a surprising 30th Annual Grammy Awards, where Michael
Jackson was shut out and Paul Simon won again for ``Graceland.''
   ``We don't see this as a peak for U2,'' lead singer Bono said
