<TEXT>
   Here are the nation's nine largest general retailers, ranked by
sales in their 1987 fiscal year, which ended Jan. 31:
   _Sears, Roebuck and Co. _ $30.21 billion.
   _K mart Corp. _ $25.63 billion.
   _Wal-Mart Stores Inc. _ $15.96 billion.
   _J.C. Penney Co. Inc. _ $13.98 billion.
   _Federated Department Stores Inc. _ $11.12 billion.
   _Dayton Hudson Corp. _ $10.5 billion.
   _May Department Stores Co. _ $10.31 billion.
   _Montgomery Ward & Co. _ $4.61 billion.
   _F.W. Woolworth Co. _ $4.17 billion.
