   The stock market posed a small gain Wednesday as the Dow Jones
average of 30 industrials finished up .83 at 2,071.29.
   The dollar strengthened in foreign exchange trading, while gold
prices were narrowly mixed. Bond prices edged higher in light
trading.
   Cocoa futures prices fell to life-of-contract lows for the
fourth consecutive day on fears that the International Cocoa
Organization will be unable to control the effects of steadily
rising production.
