<2ND_LINE>BC-Xerox Redemption,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Xerox To Redeem $366 Million In Preferred Shares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Xerox Corp. said Thursday it would redeem $365
million in preferred shares issued in 1983 to help finance its
acquisition of Crum and Forster Inc., a property and casualty
insurance company based in Morristown, N.J.
   Xerox said it would pay $52.72{ each for 6.94 million preferred
shares that pay an annual dividend of $5.45. Holders of the other
1.9 million shares of the preferred issue previously agreed to
exchange their shares for a new issue of preferred stock.
   Xerox, based in Stamford, Conn., said it financed the redemption
with money from a variety of sources, including two new series of
preferred stock issued in February and the ongoing sale of common
stock through a dividend reinvestment program.
</TEXT>
