<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Production,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
211,893 cars and trucks this week, down from last week's 215,604,
according to Ward's Automotive Reports.
   Automakers produced 254,844 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago, the trade journal said Thursday.
   They were were scheduled to make 127,727 cars this week,
compared with 130,744 a week ago and 174,376 in the same week in
1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 84,166, compared
with last week's 84,860 and last year's 80,468.
   Canadian automakers were to build 23,677 cars this week,
compared with 19,893 last week and 17,487 in the same week last
year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 20,721, compared
with 20,045 last week and 18,333 in the same week last year.
