<1ST_LINE>d f AM-BikeWheels     03-03 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bike Wheels,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bike Wheel Replacements Offered</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Also on general news wires.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A maker of 12-inch sidewalk bicycles is
offering to replace wheels that could shatter if overinflated, the
Consumer Product Safety Commission said Thursday.
   The replacement program involves about 40,000 Model BMX-12 bikes
made by Rand International of Farmingdale, N.Y., the agency said.
Bikes were sold through Otasco and other stores in the East, South
and Southeast prior to January 1987.
   The 12-inch boys' bikes are blue and can be identified by the
Rand label on the stem of the front fork.
   The safety commission said no injuries have been reported, but
there is the danger that if the tires are overinflated the rims
could shatter, causing a hazard to bystanders.
   Rand is offering free replacement wheels to consumers who write
to Rand International, 51 Executive Blvd., Farmingdale, N.Y.,
11735. Interested consumers can call Rand at 1-516-249-6000 or the
safety commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
